      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While lubricating drops can help with dry eyes, using them for several days without seeing improvement could indicate a bacterial infection like conjunctivitis, which requires prescription antibiotics. It is also possible you have a stye or a more serious condition like a corneal abrasion given the pain and symptoms, so seeing an eye doctor is crucial. Please stop self-treating and schedule an appointment with an optometrist or ophthalmologist immediately.",
      "source": "target",
