      "content": "Redness-relief drops like Visine can actually make your eyes more irritated and damage your cornea if used frequently, so they are definitely not a good management strategy. Since you mentioned crusting and pain, using Visine could mask worsening symptoms of a serious infection or injury until you reach the weekend. Please stop considering these alternatives and make an appointment with an eye doctor as soon as possible to rule out infections requiring antibiotics or surgical treatment for corneal abrasion. Your vision is too important to risk waiting.",
